span.font: The simulation represents a battle between humans and zombies who try to defeat each other
Human can kill a zombie and zombie can transform a human into a zombie
The simulation takes place on a 2D map of an island sorrouned by water
Both types of characters are described by: x coordinate, y coordinate, velocity, color, radius (when showing on the map) and a set of features individual for both classes

div.font:
If a human and a zombie come across each other on the map, they have a fight trying to defeat the other one. Mathematical model of the fight between them is comparison of battle points (BP) which can be calculated for each character based on their features. The character with bigger BP number wins. The formulas are the following:
Human:
BP = \text{strength} \cdot \left( 1+\dfrac{\text{n_killed}}{10} \right ) \cdot \left( \dfrac{\text{stamina}}{5} \right)
